<p>I'm using the gem 'clockwork' in a Rails 3.2 app. The app is running on Heroku.  The clock job runs at 1am - but it's not executing the code.</p>  <p>Here is the clock.rb code:</p>  <pre><code>  Clockwork.every(1.day, 'DailyJob', :at =&gt; '01:00'){     StatsMailer.stats_email.deliver     Forecast.where(:run_date =&gt; Date.today).each  do |forecast|       woschedules_run_jobplans_path(:id =&gt; forecast.woschedule_id)     end   } </code></pre>  <p>The log shows:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Sep 04 00:00:05 ndeavor-staging app/clock.1:  #&lt;NoMethodError: undefined method `woschedules_run_jobplans_path' for Clockwork:Module&gt;</p> </blockquote>  <p>If I rake routes, I get:</p>  <pre><code>woschedules_run_jobplans GET   /woschedules/run_jobplans(.:format) woschedules#run_jobplans </code></pre>